{
  "doc_id": "734",
  "text": "Previous research has stressed the importance of cooking skills education through the educational system [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] , however, initially the role played by the educational system was to expand upon the skills learned in the home environment [CITATION_5] . Presently, the lack of skills that children present with at school has been highlighted [CITATION_6] and a push for compulsory practical education can be seen in numerous countries [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] . It is suggested that a combination of the above methods is essential to promote the use of cooking skills and to empower individuals to prepare healthy nutritious meals to improve their diet quality as a strategy for obesity and other diet-related disease prevention and management.",
